<ol><li>A&nbsp;<b>positron-emitting isotope</b>&nbsp;is administered to the patient.</li><li>Each positron emitted meets an electron and&nbsp;<b>annihilate</b>&nbsp;each other.</li><li><b>Two gamma photons&nbsp;</b>are produced and sensed by detectors.<br></li><li>An <b>image</b> of where the positron-emitting isotopes are is built up from detector signals.</li></ol>